The evidence with the title 'Medical cannabis in the United States - Wikipedia ' says In the United States, the use of cannabis for medical purposes is legal in 33 states , plus the territories of Guam, Puerto Rico, and the Northern Mariana Islands , and the District Of Columbia, as of november 2018. Fourteen other states have more restrictive laws limiting thc content , for the  ... By 2016 , legalization of medical cannabis had spread to a majority of states . 
